-- Australia shares rise for 3rd straight day, improved data helps
-- By Swati Pandey
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 12:53AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 4 (Reuters) - Australian shares ended up 0.9 percent on Thursday led by broad-based gains sparked by data showing better-than-expected trade balance and retail sales at home. [ID:nL3N0TO15Y]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> rose about 47 points at the close of trade, also supported by signs of resilience in the U.S. economy. The benchmark ended 0.8 percent higher on Wednesday.